section.section:
The intake officer shall inform the following persons of any authorization decision specified in paragraph (1) of this subsection and the reasons for the decision:
The child who is the subject of the complaint, if practicable;
The parent, guardian, or custodian of the child who is the subject of the complaint;
The victim;
The arresting police officer; and
The person or agency that filed the complaint or caused it to be filed.

If the intake officer receives a citation other than a citation authorized under § 10-108 of the Criminal Law Article, the intake officer may:
Refer the child to an alcohol or substance abuse education or rehabilitation program;
Assign the child to a supervised work program for not more than 20 hours for the first violation and not more than 40 hours for the second or subsequent violation;
Require the parent or guardian of the child to withdraw the parent's or guardian's consent to the child's license to drive, and advise the Motor Vehicle Administration of the withdrawal of consent; or
Forward the citation to the State's Attorney.
